    There are several large, well-known, weeping cherry trees in the Kyoto Imperial Palace Park. This is a branch of the &lt;em&gt;Konoe no Shidarae Zakura&lt;/em&gt;, which translates as The Imperial Guards Weeping Cherry Tree. It sits next to a creek with a bridge in the distance. I like how the dark background makes the cherry blossoms stand out.
&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p class=&quot;jp&quot;&gt;    
   京都御所公園には、有名なしだれ桜の大木が何本かある。これは「近衛のしだれ桜」です。小川のほとりにあり、遠くに橋がかかっています。背景の水が桜を引き立てているのがいいですね。
&lt;/p&gt;</content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Kyoto" /><category term="Cherry Blossoms" /><category term="Palaces" /><summary type="html">There are several large, well-known, weeping cherry trees in the Kyoto Imperial Palace Park. This is a branch of the Konoe no Shidarae Zakura, which translates as The Imperial Guards Weeping Cherry Tree. It sits next to a creek with a bridge in the distance. I like how the dark background makes the cherry blossoms stand out.</summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2022/2203_A7R06170.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2022/2203_A7R06170.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Tenryuji・天龍寺</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/220327/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Tenryuji・天龍寺" /><published>2022-03-27T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2022-03-27T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/tenryuji</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/220327/">&lt;p class=&quot;en&quot;&gt;
    A weeping sakura tree (shidare zakura)  in front of the Tahoden Hall at Tenryuji temple. Below, some additional photos from Tenryuji this morning.
&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p class=&quot;jp&quot;&gt;    
